cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MED, cs.IR 

This paper deals with image analysis and classification using convolutional neural networks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of pre-trained models and ensemble learning suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the application of the method to medical images and specifically for glaucoma screening suggests relevance to the medical imaging (cs.MED) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
